# PROJEKT: Plastic vs. Profit
#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:2
#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:9
msgid "Life In Plastic"
msgstr "Life In Plastic"

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:10
msgid ""
"Dieses Projekt beleuchtet den Konflikt zwischen wirtschaftlichen "
"Interessen und ökologischer Verantwortung."
msgstr ""
"This project highlights the conflict between economic interests and "
"ecological responsibility."

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:19
msgid "Dein Browser unterstützt kein HTML5-Video."
msgstr "Your browser does not support HTML5 video."

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:29
msgid ""
"Die Animation zeigt die zunehmende Belastung durch Plastikmüll in den "
"Weltmeeren. Sie hinterfragt den Zusammenhang zwischen wachsendem Konsum, "
"unternehmerischem Gewinn und ökologischer Verantwortung."
msgstr ""
"The animation shows the growing burden of plastic waste in the oceans. It"
" questions the link between increasing consumption, corporate profit, and"
" ecological responsibility."

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:32
#, fuzzy
msgid "Informationen zur Plastikverschmutzung und Konzerngewinnen:"
msgstr "Information on plastic pollution and corporate profits"

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:34
msgid ""
"Plastik ist nicht nur ein Umweltproblem, sondern auch fester Bestandteil "
"globaler Wirtschaftsprozesse. Multinationale Konzerne wie Walmart, Coca-"
"Cola, Nestlé und PepsiCo nutzen große Mengen Plastik für Verpackungen – "
"vor allem bei Eigenmarkenprodukten."
msgstr ""
"Plastic is not just an environmental issue but also an integral part of "
"global economic systems. Multinational corporations such as Walmart, "
"Coca-Cola, Nestlé, and PepsiCo use large amounts of plastic "
"packaging—especially for their own-label products."

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:35
msgid ""
"Diese Visualisierung basiert auf öffentlich zugänglichen Daten und zeigt "
"eine Projektion der Plastikmengen bis 2090 unter der Annahme eines "
"„Business-as-usual“-Szenarios."
msgstr ""
"This visualization is based on publicly available data and shows a "
"projection of plastic volumes up to 2090 under a business-as-usual "
"scenario."

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:38
msgid "Kernaussagen:"
msgstr "Key messages:"

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:40
#, fuzzy, python-format
msgid ""
"2020 wurden weltweit rund 367 Mio. Tonnen Plastik produziert, davon etwa "
"23 %% (~86 Mio. Tonnen) gelangten in die Ozeane."
msgstr ""
"In 2020, around 367 million tons of plastic were produced globally, of "
"which about 23% – approximately 86 million tons – entered the oceans."

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:41
#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:51
#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:56
#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:61
msgid "Quellen:"
msgstr "Sources:"

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:46
msgid ""
"Walmart meldete im selben Jahr einen Verbrauch von rund 1,2 Mio. Tonnen "
"Plastikverpackungen."
msgstr ""
"Walmart reported using around 1.2 million tons of plastic packaging in "
"the same year."

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:47
msgid "Quelle:"
msgstr "Source:"

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:50
msgid ""
"Walmart erklärte Anfang 2025, die Ziele des US Plastics Pact "
"voraussichtlich nicht zu erreichen."
msgstr ""
"In early 2025, Walmart announced that it would likely not meet the goals "
"of the US Plastics Pact."

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:55
msgid ""
"Ohne regulatorische Maßnahmen könnte sich der globale Plastikmüll bis "
"2090 auf über 1.000 Mio. Tonnen summieren."
msgstr ""
"Without regulatory measures, global plastic waste could total over 1,000 "
"million tons by 2090."

#: templates/projekt/plastic_vs_profit/index.html:60
msgid ""
"Die Visualisierung fokussiert auf Müllstrudel (Gyres) in Pazifik, "
"Atlantik und Indischem Ozean."
msgstr ""
"The visualization focuses on ocean gyres in the Pacific, Atlantic, and "
"Indian Oceans."

